dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Includes the Tours coat of arms and the Royal coats-of-arms of France and Navarre in upper right corner of map. Title cartouche includes grape vines and the date 1620. From the Composite Atlas of France, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan. 1 map 36 x 47 cm.
dct_rights_sm: This map is in the public domain.
